[{"id":"VR817527","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a circular loop of wire with radius labeled R in a magnetic field that is directed into the page.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR817527.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A circular loop of wire of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> is placed in an external magnetic field of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> directed into the page, as shown. Over a time interval <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta t\"><math alttext=\"delta t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></math></span></span>, the magnitude of the magnetic field increases uniformly to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 B\"><math alttext=\"2 B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> and a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 1\"><math alttext=\"I sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> is induced in the loop. Then the magnitude of the magnetic field is again doubled, increasing from <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 B\"><math alttext=\"2 B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 B\"><math alttext=\"4 B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> over the same time interval <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta t\"><math alttext=\"delta t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></math></span></span>, a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 2\"><math alttext=\"I sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is induced in the loop. Which of the following is equal to the ratio of induced currents <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 2 to I sub 1\"><math alttext=\"I sub 2 to I sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR817527_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 to 1\"><math alttext=\"1 to 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 to 2\"><math alttext=\"1 to 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 to 1\"><math alttext=\"2 to 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 to 1\"><math alttext=\"4 to 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]